Executive Profile
Lorenzo A. Bettino  Director, TD Ameritrade Holding CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 12 different industries.See Board Relationships56--
Background

		Mr. Lorenzo A. Bettino, also known as Larry, was a Special Advisor and Managing Member of StarVest Partners, L.P. Mr. Bettino also served as General Partner at StarVest Partners, L.P. From 1989 to 1996, he was a Partner at Dillon Read Venture Capital, where he focused on technology and data communications investments. From 2001 to 2006, he served as Managing Director, Partner and Member of the Executive Management Group at Warburg Pincus LLC. Mr. Bettino joined Warburg ... Pincus in September 2001 and focused on investments in the information and communication technology sectors and a member of Warburg Pincus’ executive management group. He was a Partner of Ticonderoga Capital Inc. He served as a Member of the Executive Management Group at the Ticonderoga Capital Inc, comprised of the heads of all major industry groups and geographic regions. Mr. Bettino had management responsibility over the CommTech portfolio and oversaw the investment of approximately $750 million. He managed CommTech’s personnel, leading a major reorganization of the group and was responsible for the formation of Warburg’s Chief Investment Officer Advisory Council. From 1996 to 2001, Mr. Bettino was the Founding Partner of Baker Capital. He was involved in all aspects of formation, including strategic development, fundraising and operations. Mr. Bettino was responsible for hiring several of the junior investment staff for the firm. He started his investment career at Dillon Read Private Equity from 1989 to 1996, where Mr. Bettino was a Partner since 1992 and focused on early and expansion-stage investments in data communications and technology. From 1982 to 1987, he served at International Business Machines Corp. (IBM), initially as a Computer Chip Logic Design Engineer and Business Line and Account Management. He held a series of technical and management positions. He has been a Director of MediaShift since October 2010. He served as Director of Transactis, Inc. since 2010. Mr. Bettino serves as a Director of Teem Photonics S.A., FWT, LLC, Jasmine Networks, Accept Software Corporation, Curl Corp., LSSi Corp., NetOps Corp., NextPoint Networks Inc. and IRON Solutions, LLC. He serves as a Member of the Board of the Council for Entrepreneurial Development. He serves as a Member of the Board of Trustees of the Citizen’s Budget Commission. Mr. Bettino serves as a Member of the Board of Advisors of CSMG Adventi. Mr. Bettino has been an Independent Director of TD Ameritrade Holding Corporation since November 25, 2014. Mr. Bettino served as a Director of Curl, Inc. and Switchfly Inc. He served as a Director of Warburg for several companies in the portfolio, including LSSi Data CorpMACH, SA; and Telcordia Technologies, Inc. He served as a Director of S2 Systems Inc. and SS8 Networks Inc. He served as a Director of Proxim Corp. since October 2002. Mr. Bettino served as a Director of Sequoia Software Corp. since November 1999. He served as a Director of Elematics Inc. and Member of Board of Advisors at Adventis Corporation. Mr. Bettino served as a Director of Think Passenger, Inc. He served as a Director of Connected Corporation since 1999. He holds 25 years of private equity and venture capital experience and more than 23 years industry expertise in the technology and communication industries. He has significant experience in the technology areas of software, cloud-based computing, data management, application development, social media and mobility. His functional expertise has included business plan development, sales and marketing, pricing strategy and business processes and workflow. He has been a private equity investor since 1989 and responsible for investing a total of almost $850 million in private and public companies at all stages of development. Mr. Bettino has invested in both control and non-control situations and in early-stage, expansion, growth and buyout transactions in several industries, predominantly in the technology and communications sectors. Mr. Bettino received an M.B.A. degree from Harvard Business School in 1989 and a B.S. degree in Electrical Engineering from Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute in 1982.Read Full Background




